title: AlphaFold Protein Structure Retrieval and Display — af_predictions
text: uniprot_ids character() UniProt accession identifiers (uniprot_id AlphaMissense tables). tbl tibble containing information UniProt protein AlphaMissense predicted amino acid effects. av_prediction_view() tibble must columns uniprot_id, protein_variant, am_pathogenicity, am_class, tibbles returned am_data("hg38") am_data("aa_substitutions"), instance. uniprot_id must contain single unique value. af_colorfunc_by_position() tibble must columns pos value, described . bfc object created BiocFileCache::BiocFileCache(), representing location used cache PDB files retrieved av_prediction_view(). default BiocFileCache installation-wide location. pos symbol name column tbl containing amino acid residue positions protein. value symbol name column tbl containing values used coloring amino acid residues protein. pos_max integer(1) maximum residue position protein visualized. Default: maximum value pos. palette character() vector colors used visualization. default (colorspace::diverging_hcl(11)) produces colors ranging blue (low) red (high). palette_min numeric(1) value bounding minimum palette color. default minimum value; common value plotting pathogenicity might 0. palette_max numeric(1) value bounding maximum palette color. default maximum value; common value plotting pathogenicity might 1.

title: AlphaFold Protein Structure Retrieval and Display — af_predictions
text: af_predictions() returns tibble. row represents AlphaFold prediction associated corresponding uniprot accession. Columns include: entryId: AlphaFold identifier. gene: gene symbol corresponding UniProt protein. uniprotAccession, uniprotId, uniprotDescription: UniProt characterization. AlphaMissense's uniprot_id AlphaFold's uniprotAccession. taxId, organismScientificName: Organism information. uniprotStart, uniprotEnd, uniprotSequence: protein sequence information. modelCreatedDate, latestVersion, allVersions, isReviewed, isReferenceProteome: AlphaFold provenance information. cifUrl, bcifUrl, pdbUrl: URLs AlphaFold 3-dimensional molecular representations. paeImageUrl, paeDocUrl: 'Predicted Aligned Error' heat map underlying data. can used assess confidence relative orientation residues different domains, described part AlphaFold FAQ https://alphafold.ebi.ac.uk/faq af_prediction_view() displays interactive view protein RStudio panel browser tab. af_colorfunc_by_position() returns character(1) vector representation Javascript function, color vector injected.

title: AlphaFold Protein Structure Retrieval and Display — af_predictions
text: af_predictions() queries prediction endpoint AlphaFold API described https://alphafold.ebi.ac.uk/api-docs. af_prediction_view() uses tbl calculate median pathogenicity amino acid position, using am_aa_pathogenicity(). Predicted protein structure retrieved unique uniprot_id using af_predictions() pdbUrl returned function. Protein structure visualized using r3dmol https://cran.R-project.org/package=r3dmol package. Amino acids colored using aa_pathogenicity_median af_colorfunc_by_position() default palette defined interval 0, 1. af_colorfunc_by_position() uses template mechanism inject vector position-specific colors Javascript function used r3dmol::m_set_style() / r3dmol::m_style_cartoon() color residues position. Positions color specified colored 'gray'. template can seen AlphaMissenseR:::js_template("colorfunc").

title: Integrate ClinVar Labels with AlphaMissense Pathogenicity Scores — clinvar_plot
text: clinvar_plot() returns ggplot object overlays ClinVar classifications onto AlphaMissense predicted scores. Blue, gray, red colors represent pathogenicity classifications "likely benign", "ambiguous", "likely pathogenic", respectively. Large, bolded points ClinVar variants colored according clinical classification, smaller points background AlphaMissense predictions. clinvar_data() returns tbl 82872 rows 5 variables: variant_id: ClinVar variant identifier. transcript_id: Ensembl transcript identifier. protein_variant: UniProt accession:protein variant identifier. AlphaMissense: AlphaMissense pathogenicity score. label: Binary ClinVar class, either "benign" "pathogenic".

title: Integrate ClinVar Labels with AlphaMissense Pathogenicity Scores — clinvar_plot
text: alphamissense_table, columns must include: uniprot_id: UniProt accession identifier. protein_variant: variant identifier string, protein position middle, reference mutant amino acid residues left right position, respectively. am_class: AlphaMissense classification either "benign", "ambiguous", "pathogenic". am_pathogenicity: AlphaMissense predicted score. clinvar_table, columns must include: uniprot_id: UniProt accession identifier, matching alphamissense_table. protein_variant: variant identifier string, matching alphamissense_table format. cv_class: binary ClinVar classification "benign" "pathogenic".
